Second Republic lawmaker, Dr. Junaid Mohammed, has lambasted the protagonists of the security outfit Amotekun, describing it as nothing but a tribal militia to prosecute the region’s agenda of transforming into a separate nation through the backdoor. Mohammed, who spoke exclusively to Vanguard, pointed out that those behind the formation of the armed group were against the interest of Nigeria and should be made to face the full weight of the law. According to him no section of the Nigerian constitution makes provision for either state or regional police, adding that the governors have no authority whatsoever to raise such an illegal army. More details later… Vanguard News Nigeria. Second Republic lawmaker, Dr. Junaid Mohammed, has lent a voice to former President Olusegun Obasanjo’s categorisation of Nigeria’s lawmakers as corrupt and undeserving of the honour being bestowed on them by the people. July 27, 2016 In "News" Reno Omokri, the ex-media aide to Former President Goodluck Jonathan on electronic media has taken a swipe at second republic lawmaker, Junaid Mohammed who had, in a recent interview, said that should anything happen to President Muhammadu Buhari, the north will insist on being in power till 2027. May 16, 2017 In "News" IGBO leaders on the platform of Igbo Leaders of Thought, ILT, have tongue-lashed Second Republic lawmaker, Alhaji Junaid Mohammed, over what they described as his “senseless vituperations and general insult on Ndigbo.” October 29, 2014 In "News"